Task 1: Install and Configure Maltego CE
Subtask 1.1: Download and Install Maltego CE
First, we need to download and install Maltego Community Edition on our Linux machine.

Open a terminal window by pressing Ctrl + Alt + T

Update the system package list:

sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
Install Java Runtime Environment (required for Maltego):
sudo apt install default-jre -y
Verify Java installation:
java -version
Download Maltego CE from the official website:
cd ~/Downloads
wget https://maltego-downloads.s3.us-east-2.amazonaws.com/linux/Maltego.v4.5.0.deb
Install Maltego using dpkg:
sudo dpkg -i Maltego.v4.5.0.deb
If there are dependency issues, fix them:
sudo apt-get install -f
Subtask 1.2: Initial Maltego Setup
Launch Maltego from the applications menu or run:
maltego
When Maltego opens, you'll see the welcome screen. Click Register to create a free account.

Fill in the registration form with your details and verify your email address.

After email verification, log in to Maltego with your credentials.

Select Maltego CE (Free) when prompted for the product type.

Complete the initial setup wizard by accepting the terms and conditions.

