Troubleshooting Common Issues
Issue 1: Maltego Installation Problems
If Maltego fails to install:

# Remove any partial installation
sudo apt remove maltego
sudo apt autoremove

# Install required dependencies
sudo apt install default-jdk libxss1 libgconf-2-4 libxtst6 libxrandr2 libasound2 libpangocairo-1.0-0 libatk1.0-0 libcairo-gobject2 libgtk-3-0 libgdk-pixbuf2.0-0

# Try installing again
sudo dpkg -i Maltego.v4.5.0.deb
sudo apt-get install -f
Issue 2: Java Version Conflicts
If you encounter Java-related errors:

# Check Java version
java -version

# Install OpenJDK 11 if needed
sudo apt install openjdk-11-jre

# Set Java alternatives
sudo update-alternatives --config java
Issue 3: Transform Failures
If transforms don't work:

Check your internet connection
Verify that you're using Maltego CE (some transforms require paid versions)
Try using manual entity creation instead of automated transforms
Issue 4: Graph Performance Issues
For large graphs:

Use entity grouping to reduce visual complexity
Apply filters to show only relevant entities
Consider breaking large graphs into smaller, focused views
